&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Adult Mental Health and Learning Disabilities – Based in Wildwood, Worcester&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BASED AT WILDWOOD, WORCESTER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Admin Assistant &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BAND 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for people who like to be busy, work well in a team, and are able to communicate well. You will be an effective and experienced administrator; comfortable with using your own initiative, and as you will be receiving phone queries, we would like someone who has a good telephone manner, as well as good IT and administrative skills. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Post 1:            Single Point of Access – 2 x Full Time Positions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Single Point of Access (SPA) is the first point of entry for Worcestershire Healthy Minds, Community Mental Health Teams and for urgent assessments regarding people’s mental health. We cover all the whole of Worcestershire and receive referrals from qualified professionals via email. SPA also functions as a point of enquiry for agencies with regard to Worcestershire mental health services.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would love to hear from an Admin Assistant to join our friendly team to provide a professional, flexible and efficient service by supporting the existing administrative staff in post.  We are looking for someone who likes to be busy, works well in a team, and is able to communicate well. You will be an effective and experienced administrator; comfortable with using your own initiative. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will provide administrative support to the existing admin staff in dealing with all patient referrals and liaising with other healthcare professionals as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Team work together to ensure that tasks are prioritised and completed in a professional manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 2:            Neighbourhood Mental Health Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;TheNeighbourhood Mental Health Serviceis part of the Mental Health Transformation Pilot; which aims to ease referral routes and provide support in the form of triage and ongoing assessments regarding people’s mental health.  Currently the Neighbourhood Mental Health Service is being implemented within Wyre Forest, Malvern and the rural areas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would like to hear from an Admin Assistant to provide a professional, flexible and efficient service by receiving and processing referrals, booking or confirming triage appointment slots and supporting clinical staff with administrative support as required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact:  &lt;span&gt;Admin Manager: Hayley Payne on 07 590 485 709&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
